<div style="max-width: 800px; margin: auto; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">

  <h1>About This Recipe App</h1>

  <p>
    This web application was developed as part of a Rails project to demonstrate
    full-stack development using Ruby on Rails.
  </p>

  <h2>🍽️ What This App Does</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Browse recipes from different categories and regions</li>
    <li>View ingredients and measurements for each recipe</li>
    <li>Explore tags and classifications for meals</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>🔗 Data Sources</h2>
  <p>
    This app integrates multiple data sources:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><a href="https://www.themealdb.com/api.php" target="_blank">TheMealDB API</a></strong> for recipes, categories, areas, and ingredients</li>
    <li><strong>Faker</strong> for generating tags</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>⚙️ Technologies Used</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Ruby on Rails</li>
    <li>ActiveRecord & SQLite</li>
    <li>RESTful APIs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>🎯 Project Purpose</h2>
  <p>
    The purpose of this project is to demonstrate:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Database design and relationships</li>
    <li>Data integration from multiple sources</li>
    <li>Model validations and data integrity</li>
    <li>Basic Rails MVC structure</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>👩‍💻 Developer</h2>
  <p>
    Developed by Roline as part of a web development course.
  </p>

</div>